1123592943871225857.text: I like to think I’m not institutionalized, but I’m sure freedom will be an adjustment. For example, for over 5 years I’ve been locked in a cell every night all night. Freedom will be something as simple as going for a walk under the stars.

1112009599006064646.text:
I’m overwhelmed by all the birthday love and support. This helps so much. 
I hope someday I can thank each and everyone of you in the free world.

1108772167506755584.text: We set our alarms for 10pm EST every night so we can visualize my freedom for a few moments all at the same time. This is what I imagine some nights. No words can capture how good this will feel.pic.twitter.com/s3pU6IIQVl

1108042571354275840.text:
I’ve never seen a drone or self-driving car. I’ve never used AI or VR.
When I get out it will be a bit like time travel. What else has changed so far?

1107405420321136640.text: I had an amazing visit this weekend. It always feel so good to be connected to the outside. I feel sorry for the guys here who aren’t.

1106236386535858176.text: Seriously though…I’d give just about anything for even one more day outside these walls.

1106236386091237376.text: Can I just get a week off from prison? I promise I’ll come right back :P

1103713594401648640.text:
Hope still burns strong in me that I will breathe free air again.

1102985943659606016.text:
I’ve been getting so much encouragement in the mail lately 
Thank you for reminding me I’m not alone and the fight isn’t over.

1101530071708262400.text: Been a stressful few days. Just getting over a cold and I had to make a big decision with limited info. I'd love to have a crystal ball sometimes.

1100449402538254336.text: On the bus ride from the SHU to this new prison, I tried to take in the countryside and houses passing by. I wanted to savor it because I don't know when or if I'll see the free world again.

1092841769413136384.text:
I made it to a new prison! It is much better here. 
No “prison politics.” I should be able to relax and focus on my freedom.

1081658265094709248.text:
What a glorious day that will be,
A vision I can almost taste.
I’ll have a future again, I’ll be free,
And can make up for all this waste.https://twitter.com/PardonRoss/status/1067335344562020352 …

1080879512546533376.text:
At last, I’m out of the SHU (24/7 lockdown).
Now I’m in transit to what I hope is a better place. I was in for 105 very difficult days. It feels so good to have that behind me.
Unfortunately, SHUbert (my apple tree) didn’t make it out alive

1077615930333523968.text:
Merry Christmas everyone. 
This is my 6th Christmas in prison. I wish I could be out there with my loved ones. I’m still hopeful I’ll be able to celebrate at home someday.

1075813004690608128.text:
Each morning I wake up in this tiny cell, I dread facing another day.
Gratitude is the antidote I use, giving thanks just to be alive, to be healthy, to have so many wonderful people in my life. 
"Thank you" is my mantra all day. It turns dread into joy even here.

1073650253444726784.text:
SHUbert (my apple sprout) wilted last night :( My heart sank. 
He just flopped right over. I watered him and over the course of the day he stood back up! He's over 2" tall now and has 5 tiny leaves

1070736238250909696.text:
Had a good cry today. Felt in my heart "it's all gonna be ok."
Let go and the tears came.

1070005077035732992.text:
A big lesson is that others can suffer over my pain. 
Also that our actions have unforeseen ripple effects, both good and bad. 
I know also, should I be given a 2nd chance, I’ll avoid anything that could land me back in a place like this. I’ve had enough for one lifetime.

1068178279427796992.text:
Got a good cell workout going. 
Pushups, pullups, handstands, dips, lunges. 
Kills time, burns off restlessness. Hard to get enough food though.

I moved to a cell with more light and SHUbert (my apple sprout) is making a comeback! He's 2cm tall now and just starting to put out his first leaf

Got restless today. Been in this cell 40 days now.

1057671172530200576.text:
I read a few comments from some people saying: “he needs to learn his lesson.” 
I have. Every single day for the past 5 years, waking up and going to sleep in my tiny cell, I have learned my lesson many times over.

1056963230843592704.text:
SHUbert (my apple sprout) isn't growing :(

1055148356807217153.text:

1052965683636592640.text:
More than 5 weeks now back here in the hole in my little cell. I’m ok.
It hurts to be so restricted, but I refuse to suffer. 
This experience is just part of the journey back to freedom.

1050433459041136640.text:
Things took a dark turn for me a month ago. 
I’m in “the hole” in protective custody. I refused to participate in an assault which immediately turned me into a target. I’m not sure what will happen to me, but I know I made the right choice. It’s never ok to initiate violence.

I do my best to keep my head up but it’s not always easy. 
My best tools are keeping my mind focused on the here and now, praying, and staying in touch with my loved ones.

1042116713171439616.text:
Meditation is my sanctuary here in prison. 
No matter what I'm going through, when the cell door locks at night, I know I've made it safely through another day. 
I can let go of my worries, focus inward and find peace.

1041743648063287297.text:

I’m so happy for her. You’ve given many of us still on the inside hope that there is some compassion and mercy out there for us.

1040272377224065024.text: We only get 15-minute calls here, but it’s always a good feeling to be able to connect with someone from the outside. It’s like a lifeline, it reminds me there is a world outside of prison.

1039903113333760000.text:
It's all concrete, steel and stone here. 
After all these years I can barely remember how some simple things feel, like laying on a big comfy couch eating hot pizza. 
Can someone mail me a couch and a large pepperoni please?

1039613898079367168.text: Check out the interview my mom @Free_Ross did with @71RepublicMedia. Nailed it!https://71republic.com/2018/08/23/interview-lyn-ulbricht-free-ross/ …

1039197457614131200.text:
Some people ask what I plan on doing when I get out someday.
The first thing that comes to mind is a quiet, peaceful life by the beach where I can start a family. 
Beyond that, I have a few ideas about how to contribute through entrepreneurship and #CJReform activism.

1038829942866247680.text:
The fasting technique I use requires 4 hours of light cardio the 1st day. 
The last two hours I got bored and just danced around the cell to music on the radio. It felt incredible to just let loose. 
Eye of the Tiger, Rhinestone Cowboy and Time by PF got me going!

1038536494334369792.text:
The lockdown continues 
I’m 72 hours into a fast. Using the technique found in @DominicDAgosti2’s section of Tools of Titans by @tferriss, but adapted to what’s available in prison. 
Might break it tonight or tomorrow, we’ll see.

1037844427039891457.text:
The lockdown is over! 
Got some much needed fresh air and I'm able to make calls again. 
Some tweets from the lockdown are still on the way in the mail, fyi.

1037101611762368518.text:
Been locked down for a few days, so this tweet is coming through the mail. 
It sucks being trapped in a small room for days on end. 
I'm drawing, reading, exercising, writing and meditating to pass the time. 
Might start a fast tomorrow. Thinking of you all.

1034502122924998661.text:
Sometimes I reflect on my life before prison. 
All the little things I used to take for granted and the little problems I used to have. It would take a lot to upset or overwhelm me after all this. 

If I can make it through this, I feel like I can make it through anything.

1034119988175486977.text:
Every night I’m going to spend a few minutes visualizing and praying for freedom. Would you like to join me?
Set a daily alarm for 10pm EST/ 7pm PST and together we’ll imagine what it will be like to have me out there with you.

1033753799372943360.text:
Over 1,700 people have donated to promote my petition for clemency.

https://FreeRoss.org/petition pic.twitter.com/705oGAo1u4

1033388352345501696.text:
We have similar taste!

Now I know where to look when I need a new read

1033024042582736896.text:
Every day is a battle to stay hopeful and grateful for the small things. Most days I get there but some days, anxiety, anger, despair and isolation get the best of me. 

This too shall pass.

1032661523355717632.text: Got a job organizing and checking out books in the the chapel library yesterday. It doesn’t pay much but hey, it’s something to do

1032296060729810945.text: Thanks for all the home remedies! I'm feeling much better now. I think I'll try that Wim Hof breathing technique. Sounds interesting.

1031730897232453632.text: It was close but Thus Spoke Zarathustra won. I’m looking forward to reading Nietzsche for the first time and getting your recommendations in the comments. Thank you

1029757152217329664.text: Getting sick in prison is no fun  Any home remedies for a bad cough?

1029409117197164544.text: You read my mind! Family first then the internet but surfing would come before good food for me. I have never felt freer than on a big wave

1026140495066542080.text: Felt light, almost empty, yet filled with peace during my daily meditation. So grateful for it and sending that energy to you.

1024122059436126208.text: Witnessed a beautiful sunset tonight. Rays of light through clouds turning pink. It looked divine.

1023945087091322885.text: Non-violent drug offenders serving life without parole. There are many of us in here. We ask for mercy. http://freeross.org/life-sentences-for-non-violent-offenses/ …pic.twitter.com/u7M3dmEqk9

1023004366360305664.text: The murder-for-hire charge was finally dropped today. What a relief! It really hurt to have that hanging over me all these years, to be accused of being something I’m not. I just hope I won’t be seen in that light anymore. http://freeross.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Doc_14_Dismissal_Indictment_7-26-2018.pdf …

1022875763056336896.text: Fyi, I’ve been dictating my tweets over the phone and they get posted word for word. Then the comments get printed and arrive in the mail a few days later. So far, so good, but if the prison goes on an extended lockdown, I’ll have to send my tweets out via snail mail.

1022485549033041920.text: The judge who sentenced me to grow old and die in prison announced her retirement. I don’t hate you, Judge Forrest. I gave that up years ago. I hope you find happiness and peace in the next phase of your life.

1022185774794461184.text: Started a new workout routine Monday and it’s already kicking my butt. Burpee/pull-up/run today!

1021820323920936960.text: Got a batch of your comments last night at mail call. Too many to print them all! Page after page of encouragement…I’m on cloud nine  Thank you.

1021575330522439681.text: Just found out the govt moved to drop the case against me in Maryland. What a huge weight off my shoulders that will be.

1021404896136794115.text: I should be getting printouts of your comments in the mail this week. Looking forward to it. I hear there’s lots of love out there for me

1020841208774455296.text: Got a visit today. It felt so good. Almost forgot I'm locked up. It was hard to go back to the cell, but the contact with the outside is good for me. Keeps me grounded. Sorry for the 98% here who don't get visitors.

1020490315361222657.text: Wow! Almost 20k signers in the first week. This is exciting! Thank you all. Thank you mom for launching the petition. @Free_Rosshttp://bit.ly/FreeRossPetition …

1020101334987517952.text: I got 9 pages of comments from the petition in the mail tonight, and I’ve been told about all the retweets and interest in what I’m trying to do here. I am deeply moved by your response and feel the beginning of that connection I was hoping for.

1019953970771419136.text: Hi, this is Ross! I’m hoping to find my voice here after all these years of silence. It has been a strange journey, but I’m so grateful for all those who’ve shown love and support and held me up through the hard times. You give me strength. https://freeross.org/twitter-note.jpg …
